Mr. Novich has already started selling 20 overlapping facilities. He estimates that the company will start realizing the full savings � $50 million a year � from those divestitures and other cost-saving steps at the end of 2007.
In his favor: Mr. Novich credits last year's stock performance to the smooth integration of Integris. Before the deal closed, the top six executives at Ryerson and Integris put together the new management team by pulling the top talent from each of the companies. The result was a 20-member team evenly split between Ryerson and Integris executives. "We announced it early on and showed that it was a collaborative effort," he says.
�2006 by Crain Communications Inc.


