Beacon Roofing Supply Director Neil S. Novich Named to NACD’s Directorship 100 | Business Wire


























































Beacon Roofing Supply Director Neil S. Novich Named to NACD’s 
      Directorship 100






July 10, 2015 03:49 PM Eastern Daylight Time



HERNDON, Va.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. (Nasdaq: BECN) ("Beacon") announced today 
      that Director Neil S. Novich, who serves as the Chairman of Beacon’s 
      Audit Committee, has been named to the National Association of Corporate 
      Directors (“NACD”) “Directorship 100.” NACD Directorship magazine 
      each year identifies the most influential people in the boardroom 
      community, including directors, corporate governance experts, 
      journalists, regulators, and advisors. Mr. Novich joined Beacon’s Board 
      of Directors in 2012 and was named Chairman of Beacon’s Audit Committee 
      in 2013. He also was honored for his service on the Board of Directors 
      of Hillenbrand, Inc., Analog Devices, Inc., and W.W. Grainger, Inc. Mr. 
      Novich also is a Trustee of the Field Museum of Natural History in 
      Chicago.
    

      Robert R. Buck, Chairman of the Beacon’s Board of Directors, offered 
      congratulations to Mr. Novich on behalf of Beacon's Board of Directors, 
      employees and shareholders and stated: "the entire Beacon community is 
      extremely proud of Neil for being named to the NACD’s Directorship 100. 
      He is very deserving of this great honor given his extensive executive 
      and Director experience. His leadership and guidance to our Board, 
      particularly in his important role as Chairman of our Audit Committee, 
      have been and will continue to be instrumental to our Company’s growth 
      and success.”
    

      About Beacon Roofing Supply Inc.: Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. is the 
      largest publicly traded distributor of residential and non-residential 
      roofing materials and complementary building products, with 273 branches 
      in 42 states in the United States and six provinces in Canada and over 
      $2.3 billion in revenue in its 2014 Fiscal Year.
    

      "Safe Harbor" Statement under the Private Securities Litigation Reform 
      Act of 1995: Statements in this press release regarding Beacon Roofing 
      Supply Inc.'s business which are not historical facts are 
      "forward-looking statements" that involve risks and uncertainties. For a 
      discussion of such risks and uncertainties, which could cause actual 
      results to differ from those contained in the forward-looking 
      statements, see "Risk Factors" in the Company's Annual Report or Form 
      10-K for the most recently ended fiscal year.
    

      BECN-F
    

      Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc.www.becn.com


      News Provided by Acquire Media
    




Contacts

      Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc.Joseph Nowicki, 571-323-3940Executive 
      Vice President & Chief Financial OfficerJNowicki@becn.com









Release Summary
Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. announced Director Neil S. Novich, the Chairman of Beacon’s Audit Committee, has been named to the National Association of Corporate Directors (NACD) Directorship 100.






