Background

		Mr. Neil S. Novich serves as an Advisor of VisTracks, Inc. Mr. Novich served as the Executive Chairman of Ryerson Inc. since February 1999 until 2007 and also served as its President since 1995 and its Chief Executive Officer since 1995 to 2007. He joined Ryerson in 1994 as Chief Operating Officer. He was President, Chief Executive Officer and Chief Operating Officer of Ryerson Tull, Inc. from 1994 to February 1999. He was Ryerson Tull Inc.'s Senior Vice President from ... January 1995 to May 1996. He served as Senior Vice President of Inland from January 1995 to May 1996 and Vice President from June 1994 to January 1995. Prior to joining Inland in 1994, he led the Distribution and Logistics Practice of Bain & Company. He served as President of Joseph T. Ryerson & Son, Inc. from June 1994 to 2007. He spent 13 years with Bain & Company, where he spent several years as a Partner. Mr. Novich has been a Director of Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. since July 10, 2012. He serves as a Trustee of the Field Museum of Natural History and of the Children's Home & Aid Society of Illinois. He has been an Independent Director of W.W. Grainger, Inc. since 1999. He has been a Director of Hillenbrand, Inc. since February 24, 2010. He has been a Director at Analog Devices, Inc. since May 19, 2008. He served as the Chairman of J M Tull Metals Company Inc. since June 1994. Mr. Novich served as Director of Ryerson Inc. since 1994 until 2007. He served as a Director of Ryerson Tull Inc. since June 1994; J M Tull Metals Company Inc.; and MetalSite. He is a frequent speaker on strategy, enterprise risk management, executive compensation and governance. Mr. Novich earned Master of Science Degrees in both Management and Nuclear Engineering from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Physics from the Harvard University.Read Full Background




